      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding the article on the Burren, Monk's Pub in Ballyvaughan rates much more than a casual mention.</p>
        <p>Among bicyclists, Monk's Pub is a major destination. There are two attractions: the food, and the fact that by turning left out the pub's front door you can bike for miles along the coast.</p>
        <p>On our last bike trip to Ireland, my wife and I changed our plans and backtracked over 100 miles to spend two days enjoying the food and bicycling.</p>
        <p>ALBERT D. WOOD  Grantham, N.H.</p>
      </block>
